external_knowledge:
- Comprehensive building details include information such as building name, location, total floors, total area, construction year, energy rating, inspection details, and maintenance schedules;
- Latest energy audit refers to the most recent date when an energy audit was conducted;
- Most recent sensor data includes current temperature, humidity, air quality, lighting level, water consumption, and renewable energy usage;
- Active sensors are those currently operational and collecting data;
- User access history refers to the number of times a building's data has been accessed and the date of the last access.

- Energy efficiency scores are calculated based on various factors such as energy consumption, building size, and environmental impact.; 
- A higher energy efficiency score indicates better energy efficiency.; 
- The query assumes that the latest report and inspection data are the most relevant for current assessment purposes.

sql:
SELECT MAX(last_energy_audit) AS most_recent_audit_date
FROM buildings
WHERE building_id = 1;
